# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Licensed clinical corpora - NEVER COMMIT (I8)
#
# n2c2, MIMIC, i2b2 and TEHR are released under Data Use Agreements that forbid
# redistribution. A committed blob survives deletion, rebase and force-push, and becomes
# world-readable the instant this repository goes public - so the breach is not the commit,
# it is the clone. Keep these corpora outside the repo entirely; commit only synthetic
# fixtures derived from them. scripts/hooks/pre_commit_phi.sh blocks staging these paths,
# and this block is the second line of defence.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
n2c2/
mimic/
i2b2/
tehr/
*.dua

# Secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# Bearer tokens for an exposed deid-serve. deploy/container/compose.yaml mounts
# secrets/deid_bearer as a Docker secret, and the one thing that must never
# happen to a credential that authenticates a PHI endpoint is being committed.
secrets/
*.bearer

# Rust
target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# Node
node_modules/
dist/
.parcel-cache/

# The React panel's build output (bindings/panel-app/).
#
# Covered by `dist/` above, but named explicitly because that pattern is
# unanchored and reads like it is about the release tarballs in the root dist/.
# The rule is the same one bindings/wasm/pkg-web/ follows: a committed bundle is
# a bundle nobody diffs, and this one is the artifact the no-upload and CSP
# claims are checked against -- it has to be produced by the build being
# audited, not pulled from a tree. Rebuilt by `just build-panel-app`.
#
# NOTE the asymmetry with bindings/wasm/panel/, which is committed in full and
# has no build output at all. That is the point of keeping both surfaces.
bindings/panel-app/dist/
bindings/panel-app/node_modules/

# Model weights - large, and fetched explicitly via `just pull`, never committed
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.bin
*.ot
models/

# Eval build artifacts.
# WHY eval/results/*.json is NOT ignored: a committed eval run is the card contract (I5) -
# a published model card must reference an eval_sha that exists in git history. Only the
# mutable `latest.json` pointer, which is overwritten on every run, is ignored.
eval/gold/.build/
eval/results/latest.json

# Air-gapped test scaffolding generated by `just test-airgapped`
.airgap/

# Agent tooling scratch
.claude-flow/

# Detached-surface runtime state, written by scripts/surfaces.sh.
#
# logs/ holds the stdout+stderr of deid-serve and the panel server, which is the
# first place this project PERSISTS output rather than streaming it to a
# terminal. deid-serve's logger structurally cannot carry document text (I4 -
# see bindings/service/src/log.rs and the audit in docs/DEPLOY.md), but a log
# file on a machine that processes clinical text is still operational state
# about a specific deployment and not a fact about the source, so it is never
# committed. .run/ holds pidfiles and the recorded start mechanism.
logs/
.run/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editors
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.swp

# wasm-bindgen build output. Generated glue plus a multi-hundred-kilobyte .wasm,
# rebuilt by `just build-wasm` from source that IS committed. A committed binary
# is a binary nobody diffs, and this one is the artifact the no-upload proof
# runs against -- it has to be produced by the build being audited, not pulled
# from a tree.
bindings/wasm/pkg/
bindings/wasm/pkg-web/

# Local-only sample documents. NEVER COMMITTED, NEVER PUBLISHED.
#
# Real-world-shaped files used to test the parsers against documents a producer
# actually emits, rather than only against fixtures we wrote ourselves. Even when
# a file is synthetic, it does not belong in the repository: the committed corpus
# is the benchmark, and a document nobody can regenerate cannot be part of it.
# Drop local samples here and they stay here.
fixtures-local/
